         <abstract>
            <p>In this article, we prove the convergence of a splitting scheme of high order for a reaction-diffusion system of the form u&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; - M Δu + F(u) = 0 where M is an m × m matrix whose spectrum is included in &lt;latex&gt;$\{\mathscr{R}z &gt; 0\}$&lt;/latex&gt;. This scheme is obtained by applying a Richardson extrapolation to a Strang formula.</p>
          </abstract>
